(476, 1, '2018-06-21 04:47:54', '2018-06-21 04:47:54', '<strong>Ocean Edu Vietnam</strong> - the largest english language institution in Vietnam with more than 40 branches nationwide and has more than 200 qualified foreign teachers regularly conducts training to our teachers to expand their knowledge on the field and to learn with the new methodologies in teaching.\r\n\r\nOn April 20, 2018 - Ocean Edu Vietnam together with National Geographic  conducted VYL(Very young learners)  and YL(Young Learners) Training. The goal is to enhance the skills of our teacher and learn our new curriculum.\r\n\r\nThe training was conducted by Mr Michael Gough - one of the Authors of the National Geographic "HIDE and SEEK".\r\n\r\n<img src="https://scontent.fhan3-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/30713756_1122531487904406_2466895804093689961_n.jpg?_nc_cat=0&amp;oh=4efa585a436ba9fa2b8608fbf71a34c7&amp;oe=5B9C8319" alt="Image may contain: 1 person, standing" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nMr. Michael shares his knowledge and ideas in teaching Very young learners and young learners to our teachers by creating activities where our teachers act as the students.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="aligncenter" width="960"]<img src="https://scontent.fhan3-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/30738870_1122532644570957_3774112432220910772_n.jpg?_nc_cat=0&amp;oh=be125ab1eec681ce413714dbbf33c24b&amp;oe=5B6BD182" alt="Image may contain: 3 people, people sitting" width="960" height="640" /> Teacher Michael Instruct the students(Our Teachers) with this interactive game.[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="aligncenter" width="960"]<img src="https://scontent.fhan3-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/30742488_1122533054570916_1954845470916627937_n.jpg?_nc_cat=0&amp;oh=9a7c2be00c63b3e0ad2d0cc526cd2a83&amp;oe=5B9CDEE0" alt="Image may contain: 1 person, standing and indoor" width="960" height="640" /> Teacher Michael Explains the importance of TPR (Total Physical Response) language teaching approach.[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="960"]<img src="https://scontent.fhan3-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/31100511_1122531581237730_6273126930128472595_n.jpg?_nc_cat=0&amp;oh=c5df0d52df86cb4e59f6e24e7ffc68a9&amp;oe=5B5D76A1" alt="Image may contain: 4 people, indoor" width="960" height="640" /> Teachers participating during the event.[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="960"]<img src="https://scontent.fhan3-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/31044635_1122529487904606_2794452840315701931_n.jpg?_nc_cat=0&amp;oh=8a3b519e822973a5a20a9b37e31f6dde&amp;oe=5B5DD88E" alt="Image may contain: 2 people, people standing" width="960" height="640" /> Teacher Mat reinacting as "DONNA" - One of the characters in HIDE AND SEEK BOOK (National Geographic Kindy Book)[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIt was a fun-filled activity where the knowledge of our teachers has been tested through brainstorming and creating new "<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chant">Chants</a>" that suitable for very young learners and young learners.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="aligncenter" width="960"]<img src="https://scontent.fhan3-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/30727552_1122530567904498_3136965008153626035_n.jpg?_nc_cat=0&amp;oh=4aa3c43edf1832944538a38166887685&amp;oe=5B5BD40C" alt="Image may contain: 3 people, people standing" width="960" height="640" /> Teacher Michael explains the instructions to the teamleaders.[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="960"]<img src="https://scontent.fhan3-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/31036947_1122533787904176_6194211063078988763_n.jpg?_nc_cat=0&amp;oh=bf3f148d381c358481eb1d28013f3fdd&amp;oe=5B563DA6" alt="Image may contain: 8 people, people smiling, people sitting and indoor" width="960" height="640" /> Ocean Edu Teachers brainstorming during the activities.[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="960"]<img src="https://scontent.fhan3-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/30725383_1122533887904166_4064048428016293806_n.jpg?_nc_cat=0&amp;oh=87b529be652892fca6d00a49c58263c1&amp;oe=5B64226B" alt="Image may contain: 9 people, people smiling, people sitting" width="960" height="640" /> Teachers adhering with their ideas[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="960"]<img src="https://scontent.fhan3-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/30741692_1122531361237752_4039352509328514239_n.jpg?_nc_cat=0&amp;oh=2405a9e068a0d90eabdc980056331ec6&amp;oe=5B52EB71" alt="Image may contain: 1 person" width="960" height="640" /> Teacher Mitch explains the instructions to his members.[/caption]\r\n\r\nIt was an event where our teachers learned new ways to teach very young learners and young learners.\r\n\r\nMr. Michael Gough never failed to amaze our teachers and explains the beauty of activities when you put your heart into it, especially in teaching kindergarten students and living with their motto(National Geographic) - "Bringing the world to the classroom and classroom to life".\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img src="https://scontent.fhan3-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/30742016_1122533987904156_8659298949621899847_n.jpg?_nc_cat=0&amp;oh=6f84b1638e95407088359d299936c891&amp;oe=5B651E56" alt="Image may contain: 12 people, people sitting and indoor" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nOcean Edu Vietnam will always conduct training and seminars to our teachers to fuel their knowledge in teaching our students.\r\n\r\n<img src="https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/rsrc.php/v3/y4/r/-PAXP-deijE.gif" alt="Image may contain: 3 people, people standing" />See More :\r\n\r\n<iframe style="border: none; overflow: hidden;" src="https://www.facebook.com/plugins/post.php?href=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2Fmedia%2Fset%2F%3Fset%3Da.1122529441237944.1073741831.1038200639670825%26type%3D3&amp;width=100%25&amp;show_text=false&amp;height=634&amp;appId" width="100%" height="634" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe>', 'VYL and YL Teachers Training 2018', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'vyl-and-yl-teachers-training-2018', '', '', '2018-06-21 04:47:54', '2018-06-21 04:47:54', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=476', 0, 'post', '', 0),
